    "speaker": "interviewer",
    "tag": "INT 1",
    "text": "Is there anything either of you would like to say about how you feel about your mother doing this? LAURA (DAUGHTER): I think this is a very important thing that-- since she feels so strongly about telling her story, that this is a great opportunity and that a lot of people will see it now, even though she's written it all down, that it will get to many more people this way. SUSAN (DAUGHTER): I think growing up as a child, friends of mine, if their parents weren't survivors, they were never told the story. And it was like I was a celebrity to them. Tell me what happened? Your mother was involved? Your father was involved? So just the fact that this is documented for future generations-- because generations that have experienced it haven't even spread the word. It's of the utmost importance.",
