  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "PT",
    "text": "This is a photograph of my sister Laura with her school friends, which I obtained in South America. On the left side, is her friend Henye. She lives in Israel now. But she was in Montevideo at the time. And to the right, next to her, is my sister Laura, my older sister Laura. She was a very beautiful girl, highly educated, played the piano, sensitive. She was a Zionist. She was [NON-ENGLISH]. She married a very handsome young man. This was my twin brother Zygmund-- Ziggy we called him-- older by half an hour. He was almost 15 at the time, a very vital, curious young man with a sense of humor, disarming smile. He was killed.",
